SIMPLE: increase
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Increase
<hw>In*crease"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Increased</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Increasing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>incresen</ets>, <ets>encresen</ets>, <ets>enrescen</ets>, OF.
<ets>encreistre</ets>, fr. L. <ets>increscere</ets>; pref.
<ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>crescere</ets> to grow. See <er>Crescent</er>,
and cf. <er>Decrease</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To become greater or more in size, quantity, number,
degree, value, intensity, power, authority, reputation, wealth; to grow;
to augment; to advance; -- opposed to <ant>decrease</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The waters <qex>increased</qex> and bare up the ark.</q>
<rj><qau>Gen. vii. 17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He must <qex>increase</qex>, but I must decrease.</q>
<rj><qau>John iii. 30.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The heavens forbid⟦br⟧
But that our loves and comforts should <qex>increase</qex>,⟦br⟧
Even as our days do grow!</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To multiply by the production of young; to be
fertile, fruitful, or prolific.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Fishes are more numerous or <qex>increasing</qex> than beasts or
birds, as appears by their numerous spawn.</q> <rj><qau>Sir M.
Hale.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>To become more nearly full; to
show more of the surface; to wax; <as>as, the moon
<ex>increases</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Increasing function</b></col> <fld>(Math.)</fld>, <cd>a
function whose value increases when that of the variable increases, and
decreases when the latter is diminished; also called a
<altname>monotonically increasing function</altname>.</cd></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To enlarge; extend; multiply; expand; develop;
heighten; amplify; raise; enhance; spread; aggravate; magnify; augment;
advance.</syn> <usage> -- To <er>Increase</er>, <er>Enlarge</er>,
<er>Extend</er>. <xex>Enlarge</xex> implies to make larger or broader in
size. <xex>Extend</xex> marks the progress of enlargement so as to have
wider boundaries. <xex>Increase</xex> denotes enlargement by growth and
internal vitality, as in the case of plants. A kingdom is
<xex>enlarged</xex> by the addition of new territories; the mind is
<xex>enlarged</xex> by knowledge. A kingdom is <xex>extended</xex> when
its boundaries are carried to a greater distance from the center. A
man's riches, honors, knowledge, etc., are <xex>increased</xex> by
accessions which are made from time to time.</usage>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Increase</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Increase
<hw>In*crease"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To augment or
make greater in bulk, quantity, extent, value, or amount, etc.; to add
to; to extend; to lengthen; to enhance; to aggravate; <as>as, to
<ex>increase</ex> one's possessions, influence</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I will <qex>increase</qex> the famine.</q> <rj><qau>Ezek. v.
16.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Make denials⟦br⟧
<qex>Increase</qex> your services.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Increase</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Increase
<hw>In"crease</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>encres</ets>, <ets>encresse</ets>. See <er>Increase</er>, <pos>v.
i.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Addition or enlargement in size, extent, quantity,
number, intensity, value, substance, etc.; augmentation;
growth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>As if <qex>increase</qex> of appetite had grown⟦br⟧
By what it fed on.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For things of tender kind for pleasure made⟦br⟧
Shoot up with swift <qex>increase</qex>, and sudden are decay'd.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is added to the original stock by
augmentation or growth; produce; profit; interest.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Take thou no usury of him, or <qex>increase</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Lev. xxv. 36.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let them not live to taste this land's <qex>increase</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Progeny; issue; offspring.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All the <qex>increase</qex> of thy house shall die in the flower
of their age.</q> <rj><qau>1 Sam. ii. 33.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Generation.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Organs
of <xex>increase</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>The period of increasing light,
or luminous phase; the waxing; -- said of the moon.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Seeds, hair, nails, hedges, and herbs will grow soonest if set or
cut in the <qex>increase</qex> of the moon.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Increase twist</b></col>, <cd>the twixt of a rifle groove
in which the angle of twist increases from the breech to the
muzzle.</cd></cs></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Enlargement; extension; growth; development;
increment; addition; accession; production.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>increased</ent>⟦br⟧
